dering is entirely your responsibility.",[163,170,174],{"className":171,"icon":172,"title":173},[166],"noto:building-construction","Single Source of Truth","Form state lives in one canonical object.\nNo duplicated mirrors, no hidden caches, no divergence between “view state” and “data state”.",[163,176,180],{"className":177,"icon":178,"title":179},[166],"noto:top-hat","Explicity Over Implicit Magic","No hidden proxies, no auto-registration side effects.\nEvery field, mutation, and validation step is deliberate and traceable.",[163,182,186],{"className":183,"icon":184,"title":185},[166],"noto:puzzle-piece","Isolation/Modularization","Core logic, framework bindings, and utilities are separated by design.\nEach layer can evolve independently without leaking abstractions.",[163,188,192],{"className":189,"icon":190,"title":191},[166],"noto:locked-with-key","Type Safety Focused","Deep path inference, compile-time validation, and structural guarantees.\nIf a field path compiles, it exists.",[163,194,198,199,209],{"className":195,"icon":196,"title":197},[166],"noto:test-tube","Opt-in Standard Validation","Validation is pluggable and schema-driven.\nAdopt ",[200,201,205],"a",{"href":202,"rel":203},"https://standardschema.dev/",[204],"nofollow",[206,207,208],"code",{},"StandardSchemaV1"," when needed — stay lightweight when not.",[163,211,215],{"className":212,"icon":213,"title":214},[166],"noto:triangular-ruler","Determinism Over Convenience","No surprising mutations. No implicit resets.\nGiven the same inputs, the system behaves the same way — always.",[163,217,221,222,227,228,233],{"className":218,"icon":219,"title":220},[166],"noto:globe-showing-asia-australia","Framework-Agnostic","Works with ",[200,223,226],{"href":224,"rel":225},"https://react.dev/",[204],"React",", ",[200,229,232],{"href":230,"rel":231},"https://vuejs.org/",[204],"Vue",", or anything else.\nThe core does not depend on a rendering model.",[163,235,239],{"className":236,"icon":237,"title":238},[166],"noto:crossed-swords","Battle-Tested","Used in complex, deeply nested, dynamic form scenarios.\nDesigned to handle real-world edge cases without collapsing under scale.",[155,241,242,245],{},[103,243,244],{"v-slot:title":95},"Available For",[103,246,247,265,277],{"v-slot:features":95},[248,249,253,262],"u-page-feature",{"icon":250,"target":251,"to":252},"mdi:language-javascript","_blank","https://www.npmjs.com/package/@goodie-forms/core",[103,254,255,256],{"v-slot:title":95},"@goodie-form/core ",[257,258,261],"span",{"className":259},[260],"text-primary","JavaScript",[103,263,264],{"v-slot:description":95},"With FormController, it is possible to manage your form states and attach DOM elements.",[248,266,268,274],{"icon":51,"target":251,"to":267},"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@goodie-forms/react",[103,269,270,271],{"v-slot:title":95},"@goodie-form/react - ",[257,272,226],{"className":273},[260],[103,275,276],{"v-slot:description":95},"With exposed hooks, it is possible to use Goodie Forms without leaving your React environment.",[248,278,280,286],{"icon":139,"target":251,"to":279},"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@goodie-forms/vue",[103,281,282,283],{"v-slot:title":95},"@goodie-form/vue - ",[257,284,232],{"className":285},[260],[103,287,288],{"v-slot:description":95},"[WIP] Not available yet.",{"title":95,"searchDepth":290,"depth":290,"links":291},2,[],"md",{},true,"/",{"title":297,"description":298},"Goodie Forms - An unopinionated modern form state and data management library","Goodie Forms is a modern, unopinionated form state and data management library for TypeScript apps. Create flexible, type-safe forms with complete control over validation and state.","index","NBBMftELVourLutcfAJKxZKBI9T0iaSD1pBKvMg-fKA",1772227430822]